          description:
            "<p><b>Opportunity:</b></p>\n<p>WeVend is currently seeking a Full Stack Developer to develop and maintain both front-end and back-end applications which support our break through payment processing technology. This position is based at our head office location in North York, ON. WeVend is a Fintech, iOT and payment device solutions provider, enabling seamless device control and payments technologies for targeted retail verticals.</p>\n<p><b>Duties</b></p>\n<ul>\n <li>Plan, develop, optimize, and maintain web applications using a variety of programming languages</li>\n <li>Collaborate with Solutions Architect, Third Party providers, and product managers to create new functions and features that are optimize for user experience</li>\n <li>Write clean, efficient, and well-documented code for various business verticals</li>\n <li>Conduct thorough testing and debugging of applications</li>\n <li>Stay up-to-date with industry trends and technologies to ensure the best practices are implemented</li>\n <li>Integrate data from various back-end services and databases</li>\n <li>Meet established commitments and plan personal work responsibly</li>\n <li>Gather and refine specifications and requirements based on technical needs</li>\n <li>Create and maintain software documentation for releases</li>\n <li>Troubleshoot application bugs and determine/implement resolutions</li>\n <li>Optimize and refactor existing code to improve performance and reliability</li>\n</ul>\n<p><b>What This Role Requires:</b></p>\n<ul>\n <li>Ability to explain technical issues to non-technical stakeholders</li>\n <li>High attention to details while helping others do the same</li>\n <li>Ownership of your work and your projects, establishing deadlines, and communicating progress proactively</li>\n <li>Eager to research and learn in a self-directed way (always improving)</li>\n <li>Critical thinking, problem-solving and resolution</li>\n <li>Being a strong team player who works well with a wide range of people from different parts of the business, customer base, and WeVend partnerships</li>\n</ul>\n<p><b>Qualifications</b></p>\n<ul>\n <li>Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, or related field</li>\n <li>Proven experience as a Full Stack Developer or similar role</li>\n <li>Strong development skills using Angular, HTML, CSS, JavaScript, NodeJS, NextJS, Python, C++, .NET, XML, React</li>\n <li>Experience with JSON, RestAPIs, AWS APIs</li>\n <li>Experience with developing payments, e-commerce, transaction processing platforms</li>\n <li>Experience with both SQL and NoSQL database systems such as MongoDB/Amazon DocumentDB</li>\n <li>Experience using version control systems such as Git</li>\n <li>Familiarity with cloud platforms such as AWS</li>\n <li>Experience with NoSQL database systems such as MongoDB/Amazon DocumentDB</li>\n <li>Strong communication and writing skills and ability create documentation/release notes</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you are passionate about software development and enjoy working on diverse projects using cutting-edge technologies, we would love to have you join our team. We offer competitive salaries, opportunities for career growth, and a collaborative work environment that fosters innovation.</p>\n<p>Job Types: Full-time, Permanent</p>\n<p>Pay: $70,000.00-$80,000.00 per year</p>\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n<ul>\n <li>Company events</li>\n <li>Dental care</li>\n <li>Extended health care</li>\n <li>Paid time off</li>\n <li>Vision care</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Schedule:</p>\n<ul>\n <li>Monday to Friday</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Work Location: Hybrid remote in North York, ON M2N 6C6</p>",
