          title: 'Amazon Connect Developer - 100% Remote',
          description:
            "<p><b>Amazon Connect Developer — Remote</b></p>\n<p>Our client in the insurance industry is seeking an experienced Amazon Connect Developer to join their Contact Centre Infrastructure (CCI) Operations Tier 2 development team. This team is responsible for migrating Tier 2 Contact Centres from legacy infrastructure to Amazon Connect. This role requires an in-depth knowledge of cloud contact center technologies, strong development skills, and a broad understanding of enterprise infrastructure to ensure the security, stability, and supportability of services.</p>\n<p><b>What is in it for you:</b></p>\n<ul>\n <li>Hourly salary of $89 to $104, based on experience.</li>\n <li>6-month contract with the potential for permanent employment.</li>\n <li>Full-time position: 37.50 hours per week.</li>\n <li>Enjoy the flexibility of remote work.</li>\n <li>Join a passionate and inclusive team of professionals.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><b>Responsibilities: </b></p>\n<ul>\n <li>Develop and manage contact flows and skill-based routing IVR applications using Amazon Connect.</li>\n <li>Design, build, and maintain AWS Lambda functions and DynamoDB tables.</li>\n <li>Collaborate with business stakeholders to capture, design, and build requirements.</li>\n <li>Ensure the security, stability, and supportability of the contact center infrastructure.</li>\n <li>Work closely with remote teams to deliver and support cloud-based contact center solutions.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><b>What you will need to succeed:</b></p>\n<ul>\n <li>Bachelor's degree in Computer Science or a related field, or proven industry experience.</li>\n <li>3-5 years of experience in a Contact Center environment.</li>\n <li>2 years of hands-on support and development experience with Amazon Web Services (AWS), specifically Connect, DynamoDB, S3, CloudFormation, and CloudWatch.</li>\n <li>Proven experience in developing contact flows and skill-based routing IVR applications.</li>\n <li>Strong backend development skills with experience in Python, Java, and REST API.</li>\n <li>Experience with DevOps tools such as Jenkins, Ansible, and Continuous Delivery/Deployment (CDD).</li>\n <li>Familiarity with the application development lifecycle, including Agile Scrum methodology.</li>\n <li>Experience working with remote teams.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><b>Why Recruit Action?</b></p>\n<p>Recruit Action (agency permit: AP-2000003) provides recruitment services through quality support and a personalized approach to job seekers and businesses. Only candidates who match hiring criteria will be contacted.</p>\n<p># SLFJP00005087</p>\n<p>Job Types: Full-time, Fixed term contract<br>Contract length: 6 months</p>\n<p>Pay: $89.00-$104.00 per hour</p>\n<p>Expected hours: 37.50 per week</p>\n<p>Benefits:</p>\n<ul>\n <li>Work from home</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Schedule:</p>\n<ul>\n <li>8 hour shift</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Education:</p>\n<ul>\n <li>Bachelor's Degree (required)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Experience:</p>\n<ul>\n <li>Contact Center: 3 years (required)</li>\n <li>AWS Connect: 2 years (required)</li>\n <li>Legacy infrastructure: 2 years (preferred)</li>\n <li>Agile Scrum: 2 years (preferred)</li>\n <li>Back-end development (Python, Java, REST): 2 years (required)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Work Location: Hybrid remote in Toronto, ON M2J 4Y1</p>",
